==English==
===Adjective===
'''diploid'''

# {{cytology}} Of a cell, having a pair of each type of [[chromosome]], one of the pair is derived from the [[ovum]] and the other from the [[spermatozoon]]. Most [[somatic cell]]s of higher organisms are diploid.

